"<PERSON>Whitman</PERSON>?"

"Yes; he's a definite ethical force."

"Well, I'm ashamed to say that I'm a blank on the subject of <PERSON>Whitman</PERSON>.
How about you, <PERSON>Tom</PERSON>?"

<PERSON>Tom</PERSON> nodded sheepishly.

"Well," continued <PERSON>Burne</PERSON>, "you may strike a few poems that are tiresome,
but I mean the mass of his work. He's tremendous--like <PERSON>Tolstoi</PERSON>. They
