for somewhat the same things."

"You have me stumped, <PERSON>Burne</PERSON>," <PERSON>Amory</PERSON> admitted. "I've read '<PERSON>Anna Karenina</PERSON>'
and the '<PERSON>Kreutzer Sonata</PERSON>' of course, but <PERSON>Tolstoi</PERSON> is mostly in the
